<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12115b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12115b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12115b"> 115(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> les 4&deg; decimains</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> le concile de Nic&eacute;e, en 325, <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> fixa la f&ecirc;te de P&acirc;ques au premier dimanche apr&egrave;s la pleine lune qui suit l&apos;&eacute;quinoxe de printemps, et condamna comme h&eacute;r&eacute;tique tous ceux qui s&apos;opini&acirc;treraient / &agrave; prendre le jour m&ecirc;me de la pleine lune, le quatorze de Nisan, comme anniversaire de la mort du Sauveur: on les appelait les Quartod&eacute;cimains. <br><font color="green">[The Council of Nicea in 325 [&hellip;]</font> set the date of Easter as the first Sunday after the full moon which follows the vernal equinox, and condemned as heretical all those who insisted on taking the same day as the full moon, the fourteenth of Nisan, as the anniversary of the death of the Savior&mdash;these were called the <i><mark>Quartodecimans</mark></i>] <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 78-9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
